A general view of the empty Beitbridge border post near Musina, JOHANNESBURG - Home Affairs Minister, Aaron Motsoaledi, will meet his Zimbabwean counterpart at the Beitbridge border post on Friday morning. The meeting comes just days after eNCA exposed rampant corruption at the border between the two countries. The ministers will also discuss plans to tackle traffic congestion at the port of entry. EXCLUSIVE: In and out of Zimbabwe with ease The Beitbridge border post is one of the busiest on the continent. On busy days, queues of trucks can stretch for more than eight-kilometres.